headline: Is Fifth Third Bancorp (FITB) Pricing Reflect Recent Regional Bank Headlines And Growth Performance
summary: If you are wondering whether Fifth Third Bancorp is priced attractively right now, looking closely at what you are paying for each dollar of its business is a useful place to start. The stock last closed at US$50.74, with returns of 3.2% over 7 days, 4.8% over 30 days, 6.4% year to date, 19.0% over 1 year, 58.8% over 3 years, and 111.1% over 5 years, which may catch the eye of investors thinking about growth potential or changing risk perceptions.
